{
  "texts": [
    "The interesting physical phenomenon that opens up here is the possibility of fractionalization of 1-form symmetry, i.e.",
    "the induced 1-form symmetry on a q-dimensional operator O q may be a larger group G (1), or may be a larger higher-group, or the induced symmetry may actually be non-invertible.",
    "Mathematically, such q-charges are expected to form (q + 1)-representations ρ (q+1) of the 2groupG (1) associated to the 1-form symmetry group G (1). 3.",
    "The induced symmetries arise at codimension-2 (i.e.",
    "line-like) junctions of the bulk G (1) 1-form symmetry generators and O 3."
  ]
}